Architecture Reset Plan
Goal
This plan reframes AIJAH as a set of connected parts that must cooperate well:
the frontend must expose the right actions and history,
the backend loop must give the model the right amount of context,
the tools must do narrow jobs well,
the database must hold durable knowledge,
and the safety layer must stay authoritative when real file actions happen.
The point is not to chase a prettier architecture document. The point is to understand which pieces are already solid, which ones are overloaded, and which missing connections are making the agent feel inefficient.
