Expected Outcome
If this plan is followed, AIJAH should become easier to reason about as a system:
memory will be understood as several different layers instead of one vague concept,
scan data will become queryable knowledge instead of mostly prompt baggage,
the tool set will be easier for the model to use correctly,
and the architecture will support concrete jobs like duplicate detection without pretending everything must start as a full formal plan.

